main event: An unidentified object was reported over Jacksonville and Tallahassee, Florida on February 1, 1965.
interesting points: The object was reported as tracking west to east.
The tower at the local airport was alerted and additional information was requested from the air traffic control operator who witnessed the object.
The object appeared as a light, about the size of a star, and seemed to remain stationary.
The observer thought the object was a satellite.
The observer described the object as being about 500-600 feet in diameter and having colored lights around the perimeter that changed color and moved around.
sighted object: a light, about the size of a star, that seemed to remain stationary
